-- RadVision Tumbles Most in 2 Years on U.S.-Traded Shares Drop
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2011-12-15T15:10:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/radvision-tumbles-most-since-april-on-u-s-traded-shares-drop.html
RadVision Ltd. (RVSN) , the maker of video-
conferencing systems, tumbled the most in more than two years
following a drop in the U.S.-traded shares yesterday.  The shares lost 14 percent, the biggest decline since
October 2009 to 31.94 shekels, or the equivalent of $8.42 at the
4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. The stock slid 12 percent to $8.51
in New York yesterday and extended its decline another 1.9
percent to $8.35 as of 9:58 a.m. local time.  RadVision gained 19 percent this week in Tel Aviv on
newspaper reports that Avaya Inc. is in talks to buy the company
for a premium.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
